1772383734817432	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEykwk		item.move	bn-3v88	{"state":"done"}	blake3:sqLMvYtcvOrFO_KvSS2E12JxDVN7JSBW-A7SgP5zI7c
1772389511648586	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylAk		item.create	bn-2jo6	{"description":"When two workspaces created at the same epoch both modify the same file, merging them sequentially causes the second merge to silently overwrite the first's changes. The merge engine reports '1 unique path, 0 shared paths' for the second merge instead of detecting the conflict. Repro: create ws A and B at same epoch, both modify shared.txt differently, merge A, merge B — B's version wins with no warning. Expected: conflict detection on shared path.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"Overlapping edits to same file silently overwritten instead of conflict"}	blake3:uk2UzfyF7UI9piGH2lckxj-eFQs_TOnss_j3UdQpgKc
1772389560792275	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylQk		item.create	bn-2a7x	{"description":"When workspace D (created at epoch E) merges after workspace C (also created at epoch E) has already merged, D's stale version of files that C modified are treated as authoritative. This causes C's changes to be silently reverted. Repro: create C and D at same epoch, C modifies file-a, D modifies file-b (different file), merge C, merge D. Result: file-a reverts to pre-C version. The merge engine reports '2 unique paths, 0 shared paths' — it should detect that file-a was modified in the epoch between D's creation and merge, and either skip it or flag a conflict. This is the documented 'stale workspace reversion hazard' and it affects ALL merges of stale workspaces, even when they modify different files.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"Stale workspace merge silently reverts other workspace changes"}	blake3:mvN7J3hRWVKHb4NEmQH69BgLns5K5ugDWZ6yTGsYCP0
1772389600498465	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylgk		item.create	bn-2ydi	{"description":"bn-1zdc was marked as done but the behavior persists: running 'maw ws merge no-change --destroy' on a workspace with zero changes reports 'No changes detected' and 'Workspaces were not destroyed' — the workspace survives despite --destroy. The error message also does not suggest 'maw ws destroy <name>' as a workaround. Either: (1) respect --destroy and destroy the workspace even with no changes, or (2) suggest the explicit destroy command in the error output.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"No-change merge with --destroy still does not destroy workspace (bn-1zdc regression)"}	blake3:QN0O4apONfTgtUZ_hoQjZ9q3wB0pQHE7InekHjBAGE8
1772389614208607	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEylwk		item.create	bn-34fc	{"description":"bn-2axt was marked as done but the error message is unchanged. Running 'maw ws conflicts destroy-test' on a destroyed workspace gives: 'Error: prepare phase failed: PREPARE: HEAD not found for workspace destroy-test: spawn git: No such file or directory (os error 2)'. Expected: a clear message like 'Error: workspace destroy-test does not exist'. The 'spawn git' error leaks implementation details and confuses users.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"ws conflicts on destroyed workspace still gives spawn git error (bn-2axt regression)"}	blake3:fT6JVvpbOTQK6n9yJI6-2BxNx1QcD4BEjoWsPoqZkgU
1772389635489986	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymAk		item.create	bn-3bo8	{"description":"bn-2ge6 was marked done but ws diff still doesn't show untracked new files. It now shows modified tracked files that are uncommitted (improvement), but a brand new untracked file (e.g., echo 'content' > ws/test/new.txt) does not appear in ws diff output. The merge engine DOES pick up these files during merge, so the diff and merge views are inconsistent. Repro: create workspace, add new file without committing or staging, run maw ws diff — file not shown. Stage with git add — still need to verify if that helps.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"ws diff does not show untracked new files (partial bn-2ge6 regression)"}	blake3:3Q-_RntvdEGTtq_BTQa7W6n0wRxyB7__VlY1OsDKhew
1772389667668838	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymQk		item.create	bn-14tx	{"description":"bn-3qeh was marked done but 'maw status' still shows non-default workspaces without stale annotations. 'maw ws list' correctly shows '(stale)' annotation and a WARNING about stale ephemeral workspaces. 'maw status' just shows '- stale-check' with no staleness indicator. Expected: 'maw status' should include the (stale) annotation inline, matching what ws list shows.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"maw status still does not annotate stale workspaces (bn-3qeh regression)"}	blake3:B67XbQRNlOG_eJBzlqz-QJtL8S0GldGX6287qwjHdgI
1772389709106533	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymgk		item.create	bn-3voq	{"description":"bn-3v88 was marked done but: (1) 'maw gc --refs' does not exist (error: unexpected argument '--refs'), gc only handles epoch snapshots. (2) After creating and destroying 15+ workspaces, 19 stale refs/manifold/head/* refs and 12 recovery refs accumulate with no cleanup mechanism. (3) 'maw doctor' reports 'All checks passed\\!' despite the stale refs. (4) Running 'maw gc' from repo root fails with 'Not in a git repository' since it's a bare repo — must run from ws/default. Need: a ref pruning command and doctor should flag accumulated stale head refs for destroyed workspaces.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"gc --refs not implemented and stale refs still accumulate (bn-3v88 regression)"}	blake3:Nb7KVFWNU_E-n6WSP1rNryJ7KB767VbBlsgkG3YjkHE
1772389715857783	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEymwk		item.create	bn-1ktc	{"description":"Running 'maw gc' from the maw repo root (/tmp/test-repo/) fails with 'Error: Not in a git repository: fatal: this operation must be run in a work tree'. The repo root is a bare git repo structure (.git/ directory, ws/ directory) so some commands that internally run git worktree operations fail here. Must run from ws/default/ instead. Other commands like 'maw status', 'maw ws list', 'maw ws create' work from root. gc should also work from root or provide a clear error message about running from a workspace.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"maw gc fails from repo root with 'Not in a git repository'"}	blake3:pAZfquQe_H8MAnLBsBA8QuWWkxy_2ZoBmJlJW1v1_yc
