1772390029203893	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyoAk		item.create	bn-27zn	{"description":"When running 'maw ws merge <name> --destroy' on a workspace with no changes, the merge correctly reports 'No changes detected' but does NOT honor the --destroy flag. The workspace remains listed in 'maw ws list' and the directory persists. Expected: --destroy should destroy the workspace regardless of whether there are changes to merge. Repro: maw ws create no-change; maw ws merge no-change --destroy; maw ws list (still shows no-change)","kind":"bug","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"ws merge --destroy does not destroy workspace when no changes detected"}	blake3:CA9zVqK8dCHI8EdutKSJ9b26mrKMZ5gXyqrXrwPlh6s
1772390041410981	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyoQk		item.create	bn-3bj0	{"description":"Running 'maw ws conflicts <name>' on a destroyed workspace produces: 'Error: prepare phase failed: PREPARE: HEAD not found for workspace temp-ws: spawn git: No such file or directory (os error 2)'. Expected: A clean error like 'workspace temp-ws does not exist'. The error leaks internal implementation details (spawn git) to the user.","kind":"bug","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"ws conflicts on destroyed workspace shows 'spawn git' error instead of 'does not exist'"}	blake3:fzAT-_puzP07yIjG8A4phhpvSPZ6EgXo4PdoZmo0KLs
1772390078885104	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyogk		item.create	bn-onw5	{"description":"After merging a workspace (advancing epoch), 'maw status' lists remaining workspaces but does not annotate them with '(stale)' when their epoch is behind the current epoch. Expected: stale-check-b should show as 'stale-check-b (stale)' or similar. The status output shows '[WARN] Non-default workspaces: 1 / stale-check-b' but no staleness indication. This is the bn-3qeh fix that is not yet working.","kind":"bug","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"maw status does not annotate stale workspaces"}	blake3:-lf-zLS7GSBm2zotLnx19FDcdvIFjsqsR8Ag4Xe0rik
1772390359346267	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyowk		item.create	bn-1k7n	{"description":"When merging 5 stale workspaces sequentially (all created at the same epoch, each touching the same file merge.rs), the epoch-delta injection does not correctly prevent later workspaces from reverting changes made by earlier ones. Crystal-crane added --destroy fix at line 2073, shadow-otter added existence check at line 1676 — but shadow-otter's merge reverted crystal-crane's additions. The diff3 auto-resolve should have merged both changes (non-overlapping regions), but instead the workspace version won entirely. Root cause likely: the epoch-delta synthetic PatchSet content or base override is incorrect, causing diff3 to see a misleading base that favors the workspace side.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-2"],"title":"Epoch-delta injection fails to prevent reversion in sequential stale merges","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:vZSOexJov_Etkpb1mWJZsWoR9nHk9PDwRCQ1S5h_yo8
