1772390364930206	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqAk		item.move	bn-2a7x	{"state":"done"}	blake3:EuN7cvnNyDw8bRP3rZQrUE8JhZHtCsS2Jd6KvaMyJAs
1772392752693225	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqQk		item.comment	bn-1k7n	{"body":"ROOT CAUSE FOUND: The sequential merges were executed with the OLD maw binary (pre-iron-tiger, 0.49.0 without epoch-delta injection code). The epoch-delta fix was in the source code (committed via iron-tiger merge at 9caee3f9) but the binary was not rebuilt before the 5 sequential workspace merges. The old binary had no stale-workspace protection — it used the workspace's version verbatim for overlapping files. After rebuilding the binary, comprehensive reproduction tests confirm the epoch-delta mechanism works correctly: stale workspaces trigger 'shared path' detection, diff3 cleanly merges non-overlapping changes, and no data is lost. This is an operational/workflow issue (binary not rebuilt), not a code bug."}	blake3:fromTLMP45AOExRLcIIl3_DqXCpVr23FWEq0pKYDx9w
1772392755307340	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqgk		item.move	bn-1k7n	{"state":"done"}	blake3:4pCdkL6PYKN3wLU7BKHt3teMglOCroZZXR3TqyVmLxU
1772393496334266	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyqwk		item.create	bn-2cv5	{"description":"## Bug\n\nWhen two stale workspaces modify the same line of the same file differently, the merge engine may silently resolve the conflict to the base (original) version instead of reporting a conflict.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n1. Create test repo: git init && git commit --allow-empty -m init && maw init\n2. Create a file with content (e.g., utils.rs) and commit in ws/default/\n3. maw epoch sync\n4. maw ws create ws-c1 && maw ws create ws-c2 (same epoch)\n5. In ws-c1: change line 1 comment AND keep the rest the same. Commit.\n6. In ws-c2: change line 1 comment differently AND rewrite a function body. Commit.\n7. maw ws merge ws-c1 --destroy (clean adopt)\n8. maw ws merge ws-c2 --destroy (stale, should conflict on line 1)\n\n## Expected\n\nStep 8 should report a conflict on line 1 since both ws-c1 (via epoch) and ws-c2 changed it differently from the base.\n\ngit merge-tree --trivial-merge confirms the conflict exists (shows <<<<<<< markers).\n\n## Actual\n\nStep 8 resolves to '1 shared path(s), 1 resolved' with NO conflict. The result contains the BASE version of line 1 (neither ws-c1 nor ws-c2's change). Both sides' changes to that line are silently lost.\n\n## Impact\n\nSilent data loss — changes from a previously-merged workspace can be silently reverted when a stale workspace's merge auto-resolves a region that git's merge-tree would flag as conflicting.\n\n## Test environment\n\nmaw 0.49.0, git 2.53.0, test repo in /tmp/","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-3"],"title":"Merge engine silently resolves conflict to base when git merge-tree detects conflict"}	blake3:T-3jXeCarS7qi-6ISdf_hqjyYj_fuAuNxFLYSn_U7UI
1772393504258762	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrAk		item.create	bn-2fd1	{"description":"## Bug (Minor / UX)\n\nAfter running 'maw ws merge X --destroy', immediately running 'maw ws merge Y' produces a warning:\n\n  WARNING: stale merge-state found at phase 'commit' but epoch ref already advanced — previous merge completed without cleanup. Clearing stale state.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n1. maw ws create repro-1 && maw ws create repro-2\n2. Make changes in both, commit\n3. maw ws merge repro-1 --destroy\n4. maw ws merge repro-2\n\nStep 4 shows the WARNING. The merge still succeeds, but the warning is confusing.\n\n## Expected\n\nThe --destroy flag should fully clean up merge state as part of its cleanup phase, so the next merge starts with no stale state.\n\n## Actual\n\nThe merge state from the previous merge (at phase 'commit') persists until the next merge detects and clears it.\n\n## Impact\n\nLow — the merge still works. But the warning may confuse automated agents or users into thinking something went wrong.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-3"],"title":"Stale merge-state warning after --destroy merge followed by immediate next merge"}	blake3:HhZIPSysW-FtXYeSnE3rUoRDsTs2kmTldUV4Ukv-n3w
1772393514392150	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrQk		item.create	bn-1r81	{"description":"## Bug (Minor / UX)\n\nWhen ws/default/ has uncommitted changes and a workspace is merged, the merge succeeds and replays the uncommitted changes (with message 'User work replayed successfully'). However, the resulting git state in ws/default/ is confusing: some files are staged, some are unstaged.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n1. echo '// uncommitted' >> ws/default/src/utils.rs  (do NOT commit)\n2. maw ws create ws-test\n3. echo '// ws-test' >> ws/ws-test/src/main.rs\n4. cd ws/ws-test && git add -A && git commit -m 'change'\n5. maw ws merge ws-test --destroy\n6. cd ws/default && git status\n\n## Expected\n\nAfter merge, ws/default/ should have the uncommitted change as an unstaged modification (clean replay).\n\n## Actual\n\ngit status shows both 'Changes to be committed' (staged) and 'Changes not staged for commit' (unstaged) for different/same files. This mixed state can confuse automated agents that check git status.\n\n## Impact\n\nLow — the actual data is correct and the uncommitted change is preserved. But the git state could confuse tooling.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-3"],"title":"Merge with uncommitted default changes leaves mixed staged/unstaged git state"}	blake3:za7opJ4wgyBVfd9yI40tGhCf5tcosWhXQNX90oimIsk
1772393567956163	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrgk		item.create	bn-1wqe	{"description":"## Bug\n\nThe 'maw ws status' global-view line shows the wrong epoch OID when stale workspaces exist.\n\n## Reproduction\n\n1. maw ws create ws-a\n2. Make changes in ws-a and commit\n3. maw ws merge ws-a --destroy  (epoch advances from E0 to E1)\n4. maw ws create ws-b (created at E1)\n5. maw ws create ws-c (created at E1) \n6. Make changes in ws-b and commit\n7. maw ws merge ws-b --destroy (epoch advances from E1 to E2)\n8. maw ws status\n\n## Expected\n\nThe global-view line should show the current epoch E2 (matching what refs/manifold/epoch/current points to).\n\n## Actual\n\nThe global-view line shows E1 (the stale workspace's creation epoch), not E2 (the current epoch).\n\nExample output:\n  global-view: epoch=E1_SHORT ws=2 patches=1 conflicts=0 ops=5\n  default  epoch:E2_SHORT [persistent]  (default)\n\nThe default workspace line correctly shows E2, but the global-view line shows E1.\n\n## Impact\n\nMedium — misleading for automated tools that parse the global-view epoch. Agents may think the epoch hasn't advanced.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-3"],"title":"ws status global-view shows wrong epoch when stale workspaces exist"}	blake3:h5UP0umAjHetoq6PXjQYnI6g-Ts3xEqIa_INEdtenk8
1772394992099754	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyrwk		item.comment	bn-2cv5	{"body":"FIXED: Added interstitial_differs() check in AST merge. When variants modify text between named items (comments, file headers), the AST merge now falls back to diff3 which correctly detects conflicts. Non-overlapping function changes still merge cleanly via AST."}	blake3:ZJRGBEP1eQD5bTdKztMvPGRCw7spwhkTYtt3SjIE5dY
1772394992124853	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysAk		item.move	bn-2cv5	{"state":"done"}	blake3:PrEXo5nmxF49RxVW9F1A8__pq4NOy1XuTqtx7CUssR0
1772395372245313	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysQk		item.create	bn-13qz	{"description":"sim-test-4 test 1: When ws-a and ws-b both modify a file-level comment (interstitial text) in the same file plus different function bodies, merging ws-a then stale ws-b produces the BASE version of the file. ALL changes from both workspaces are silently lost. No conflict is reported -- the merge engine reports '1 shared path, 1 resolved' but the result is byte-for-byte identical to the original base. This is a severe data loss scenario. Expected: (1) the comment change should be a CONFLICT since both changed it, (2) non-overlapping function body changes should merge cleanly, (3) at minimum the merging workspace's own changes should survive.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-4"],"title":"stale merge reverts ALL changes when both workspaces modify interstitial text in same file"}	blake3:5SBuSeF_JmmC5WtqfgGtgJNC73Ry9v6QC5ucJ5GFd1k
1772395379698276	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEysgk		item.create	bn-1ldh	{"description":"sim-test-4 test 12: When two stale workspaces each add a different 'use' declaration adjacent to an existing 'use std::collections::HashMap;' at line 7, the AST merge engine places the new use declarations at lines 62-64 (end of file) instead of near line 7 where they were inserted. Both declarations survive but their placement is incorrect. Expected: new use declarations should be placed near the existing use block, not appended at file end. The merge engine appears to treat new use_declaration AST nodes as appendable items rather than preserving their inter-node position.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-4"],"title":"AST merge appends use declarations at EOF instead of preserving source position"}	blake3:vcFzUikcRytQIjjYpjfvrBBcZSahmU9vuQp8fPHV0kE
1772395385305248	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyswk		item.create	bn-3vmr	{"description":"sim-test-4 test 5: When two stale workspaces each append a new function (with doc comments) to the same file, the AST merge preserves the function bodies but strips the /// doc comments above them. For example, '/// Check if a number is prime.' before pub fn is_prime() and '/// Calculate the nth Fibonacci number.' before pub fn fibonacci() both disappear. The functions themselves merge correctly. Expected: doc comments (which are interstitial text attached to function items) should be preserved during AST-level merging.","kind":"task","labels":["sim-test-4"],"title":"AST merge strips doc comments from newly-added functions during stale merge"}	blake3:YaHAgy5rRN75nvNQDSwVUeVsBaPf3Gul9gAPPIV_Crg
1772395496421389	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytAk		item.comment	bn-13qz	{"body":"Cannot reproduce with current binary (post-bn-2cv5 fix). The interstitial_differs() check correctly causes AST merge to fall back to diff3 conflict. Likely the sim-test-4 agent ran before the fix was installed."}	blake3:XTOUKqEGTvvsq0cg-zm-HdIUjqPgr_UB3dq7T6lHvaM
1772395496442277	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytQk		item.move	bn-13qz	{"state":"done"}	blake3:7karyzdsTcQMNwgaOjkFBQ6eEfnFrMkfQtE8kJ_HUt4
1772395810949566	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytgk		item.comment	bn-3vmr	{"body":"FIXED: Added leading_trivia() helper that extracts doc comments and attributes preceding a function node in the variant source. reconstruct_merged_file now prepends trivia when appending Added items."}	blake3:caeMRlliR1MqhdjnuHkmCUTt192GcpZMj2HCJVHz8UI
1772395810975340	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEytwk		item.move	bn-3vmr	{"state":"done"}	blake3:S0FdqEHrE0X-XjQ4BGg0hBQW8XPqK640qSLhL5cdhLk
1772395810994939	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyuAk		item.comment	bn-1ldh	{"body":"FIXED: New use declarations are now inserted after the last surviving use_declaration in the result rather than appended at EOF. Falls back to EOF when no anchor use exists (e.g. all base uses were deleted)."}	blake3:8KgEEzwYCOEEenTat2P9sr5GvHFsLOIGBR46-PmjvFM
