1772396815344787	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEz7QE		item.create	bn-1dkl	{"description":"we allow this... maybe we shouldn't, but it's ok for now.\nby default the commit message is like \"epock: merged <ws>\" or something.\nagents tend to leave this. we don't know exactly what happened.\n\nin lieu of requiring --message we should:\n- show something like NOTICE: merged with commit message \"...\"\n- show something like \"To ammend this commit run ...\"\n\nshould we have a maw subcommand to do that easily instead of requiring git?","kind":"task","labels":["merge","ux"],"title":"if someone does `merge` without --message, show more help"}	blake3:pXrQZ6PDDNcQVbq_t_N3H5K0a11ViPMJ6b2I9MPg1G0
1772397120619540	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyugk		item.create	bn-39r3	{"description":"## Bug\n\n`build_tree()` in `crates/maw-core/src/merge/build.rs` line 413 sorts tree entries with simple lexicographic name comparison:\n\n```rust\ntree_entries.sort_by(|a, b| a.name.cmp(&b.name));\n```\n\nThis violates git's tree sorting rule: directory entries must sort as if they have a trailing `/` character. For example:\n- `assurance` (tree) sorts as `assurance/` → should come AFTER `assurance-plan.md`\n- But simple name comparison puts `assurance` BEFORE `assurance-plan.md` (because string ends < `-`)\n\n## Impact\n\nCreates malformed tree objects that pass local git fsck but are **rejected by GitHub** (`treeNotSorted: not properly sorted`), blocking pushes. Any merge where a directory and similarly-prefixed files coexist in the same parent directory will produce a corrupt tree.\n\n## Discovered via\n\nRelease v0.50.0 push was rejected by GitHub. Object `ce1c10d4` (the `notes/` tree) had `assurance` (tree) sorted before `assurance-near-proof-proposal.md` (blob). Three merge commits (`fix-reverts`, `bn-2cv5-fix`, `ast-fix`) were affected.\n\n## Workaround applied\n\nManually rebuilt the affected tree with `git mktree` (correct sort order), then used `git commit-tree` to rewrite the 3 affected commits + 2 descendants. History was rewritten before any push, so no force-push needed.\n\n## Fix\n\nLine 413 of `crates/maw-core/src/merge/build.rs`:\n\n```rust\n// Current (WRONG):\ntree_entries.sort_by(|a, b| a.name.cmp(&b.name));\n\n// Correct:\ntree_entries.sort_by(|a, b| {\n    let a_key: String = if a.mode == maw_git::EntryMode::Tree {\n        format!(\"{}/\", a.name)\n    } else {\n        a.name.clone()\n    };\n    let b_key: String = if b.mode == maw_git::EntryMode::Tree {\n        format!(\"{}/\", b.name)\n    } else {\n        b.name.clone()\n    };\n    a_key.cmp(&b_key)\n});\n```\n\n## Test needed\n\nAdd a test that creates a merge where a directory and similarly-named files coexist (e.g., `notes/assurance/` alongside `notes/assurance-plan.md`), then verify the resulting tree passes `git fsck --strict`.\n\n## Files\n- `crates/maw-core/src/merge/build.rs:413` — the sort line\n- `crates/maw-git/src/objects_impl.rs:125` — `write_tree()` which receives pre-sorted entries\n- `crates/maw-git/src/types.rs:218` — `EntryMode` enum for checking Tree vs Blob","kind":"task","title":"Merge build_tree() uses wrong sort order for git tree entries"}	blake3:YUF90KxQ_vZQ12H2bdQuLNgmti9iCzu7fYGjNhI-5rs
