1772414544506349	bob	itc:v3:AWKSc8kyZJPJk5EAAAAAQau9WtV610AAAAEz7gE		item.create	bn-15od	{"description":"may ui shows:\n\nNo workspaces\n\nmaw status shows:\n\n=== maw status ===\n✓ Non-default workspaces: none\n⚠ Working copy: 18 changed files\n  - crates/maw-git/src/index_impl.rs\n  - .bones/events/2026-03.events\n  - Cargo.lock\n  - Cargo.toml\n  - crates/maw-assurance/Cargo.toml\n  - crates/maw-cli/Cargo.toml\n  - crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/diff.rs\n  - crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/merge.rs\n  - crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/status.rs\n  - crates/maw-cli/src/workspace/working_copy.rs\n  - crates/maw-core/Cargo.toml\n  - crates/maw-core/src/merge/build.rs\n  - crates/maw-git/Cargo.toml\n  - crates/maw-git/src/gix_repo.rs\n  - crates/maw-git/src/lib.rs\n  - crates/maw-git/src/repo.rs\n  - crates/maw-tui/Cargo.toml\n  - src/merge/prepare.rs\n✓ Untracked files: none\n⚠ Main vs origin: ahead by 1 (not pushed)\n✓ Default workspace: fresh\n","kind":"bug","labels":["ui"],"title":"maw ui not working"}	blake3:9YyHTQrXnBTKbZUxba5lwBZNP0zUap6S4qi9F0XAP94
1772421676026445	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEywwk		item.create	bn-3pia	{"description":"When maw writes git refs via gix (refs/manifold/*, refs/heads/main, etc.), the ref files lack a trailing LF byte. git fsck reports 'refMissingNewline' warnings for every ref. While not a data integrity issue, it is noisy and could confuse users running fsck. Repro: create any workspace, merge it, run 'git -C repo.git fsck'. Expected: refs end with LF. Actual: refs end with hex OID only, no trailing newline.","kind":"task","title":"gix ref writes lack trailing newline (git fsck warns)"}	blake3:D1ltZ60Cw4RD6vEGOAV0BqX7jhytJHKVqeCs_Wp97qE
1772422047126751	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyxAk		item.create	bn-2iux	{"description":"When 'maw ws list' shows a workspace as '(ready to merge)', it could also indicate whether the merge would have conflicts — e.g. '(ready to merge, 0 conflicts)' vs '(ready to merge, conflicts likely)'. This would save agents an extra 'maw ws merge --check' round-trip. Implementation: run the overlap/conflict check against epoch during list and annotate the output.","kind":"task","title":"ws list: show conflict likelihood for merge-ready workspaces"}	blake3:n-tcRpr_7L7yaoWH-s3qpkjCg7ZSZ02nxitHdhVwxDA
1772422478484353	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyxQk		item.create	bn-14yf	{"description":"When a stale workspace has commits, 'maw ws sync' currently refuses. Add '--rebase' that replays workspace commits onto the current epoch.\n\nKey design constraint: conflicts are DATA, not workflow blockers (jj-style). When a replayed commit hits a conflict:\n1. Record the conflict in the oplog (ConflictDetected op with base/ours/theirs content, file path, commit being replayed)\n2. Write conflict markers to the working tree file (so the agent can see and edit them)\n3. Continue replaying remaining commits (they may or may not touch the conflicted file)\n4. Mark workspace as 'conflicted' in manifold metadata\n\nWorkspace in 'conflicted' state:\n- 'maw ws status' / 'maw ws list' shows conflict indicator with count\n- 'maw ws conflicts <name>' lists all unresolved conflicts from the rebase\n- Agent edits conflicted files, removes markers, commits\n- 'maw ws merge' refuses until conflicts are resolved (or --force)\n- Conflicts can be resolved one-at-a-time or all-at-once\n\nOplog integration:\n- Each replayed commit becomes a RebaseReplay op in the oplog\n- Conflicts become ConflictDetected ops with full base/ours/theirs capture\n- Resolution becomes ConflictResolved op\n- Full rebase is recoverable: oplog has the pre-rebase state\n\nThis prevents the 'stale workspace is permanently stuck' problem while keeping agents unblocked. No interactive prompts, no half-finished git rebase state to clean up.","kind":"task","title":"ws sync --rebase: conflict-as-data rebase for stale workspaces"}	blake3:G48K6YGRbfRDPAXIcCNz1O6IntMM7PLGzWukLJQHluI
1772423030895884	maw-dev	itc:v3:AWKTmSTM_JOSSTQAAAAAQa7Vbfq6qsAAAAEyxgk		item.move	bn-3pia	{"state":"done"}	blake3:hyz7Q-U1uoGEpWVE0Z-otCpVPd1ns0gxKJ-FrqSlmQY
