1772858741342313	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEyoQE		item.create	bn-beu5	{"description":"Address field-validated correctness gaps found while exercising the new explicit changes workflow in fresh /tmp repos. Scope includes epoch/main semantics for merge --into change targets, stale/sync status consistency, push --advance safety, snapshot collection robustness for directory paths, and end-to-end regression coverage/docs updates.","kind":"goal","labels":["changes-model","reliability","safety"],"title":"Harden explicit changes workflow after /tmp field eval"}	blake3:LmF4HCwgc-MbDh3pcqn9VfVMU2VMfbbEI139IejbKGY
1772858750982111	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEyogE		item.create	bn-3092	{"description":"Repro in fresh repo: create change from main, create bound workspace, commit, then run 'maw ws merge <ws> --into <change-id> --destroy'. Current behavior advances refs/manifold/epoch/current to change-branch candidate while refs/heads/main stays put, causing global epoch to track non-main history. Expected behavior for trunk-oriented model: merge-into-change should not re-point global epoch/main away from trunk; only merge-into-default should advance epoch/main. Implement corrected commit/ref update semantics for non-default targets and ensure no data-loss invariants remain intact. Acceptance: after merge into change, main and epoch relationship matches defined contract; merge output reflects target branch accurately; no implicit promotion to trunk occurs.","kind":"bug","labels":["changes-model","merge","correctness"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"l","title":"Fix epoch/main drift when merging workspace into change target"}	blake3:w5YDTiFe12eu4ud8_aovPU1VmqvxbX9SgfuJYoLw1pk
1772858757958617	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEyowE		item.create	bn-3dlb	{"description":"Repro after merge-into-change flow: 'maw ws status' and 'maw ws merge <change-ws> --into default --check' report workspace is behind main and instruct 'maw ws sync <ws>', but sync replies 'Workspace is up to date'. Users get stuck in contradictory guidance. Align stale detection, merge readiness checks, and sync eligibility so diagnostics are consistent with actual HEAD/epoch/base relationships for change-bound workspaces. Acceptance: same workspace state yields consistent result across ws status, ws list, ws merge --check, and ws sync; suggested remediation command succeeds or no remediation is suggested.","kind":"bug","labels":["changes-model","status","sync"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"m","title":"Eliminate stale/sync contradiction for change workspaces"}	blake3:fLQzLa79wgYeHFWywQAsvYWsDgY3yFW-hvVruid57sU
1772858763940349	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEypAE		item.create	bn-1lnn	{"description":"Current behavior can suggest and allow 'maw push --advance' to fast-forward main to epoch even when epoch came from merge-into-change flow, which may unintentionally land change work on trunk. Add explicit safety checks so push guidance and push execution respect explicit-target workflow boundaries. Acceptance: push hinting distinguishes 'epoch ahead due to change-target merge' from normal main-ahead state; unsafe advance is blocked or requires explicit override with clear warning; safe trunk pushes remain one-command for normal merge-into-default flow.","kind":"bug","labels":["changes-model","push","safety"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"m","title":"Add guardrails for maw push --advance after non-default merges"}	blake3:pwil2j4gvf0YcIKVuhtu9t8ffLDY8B5YgSicVVoiqj0
1772858772541618	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEypQE		item.create	bn-hhc4	{"description":"Repro: inside workspace create nested git dir (for example .tmp/sub/.git) plus a normal committed change, then merge workspace. PREPARE fails with 'failed to read ... Is a directory (os error 21)' while collecting snapshots. Update snapshot/dirty-path handling to ignore or correctly classify directory entries (including nested repos/tooling dirs) instead of attempting file reads. Acceptance: merge proceeds when only file paths are relevant; directory-only entries do not crash PREPARE; regression test covers nested .git and generic directories.","kind":"bug","labels":["merge","snapshot","robustness"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"m","title":"Handle directory paths safely in merge PREPARE snapshot collection"}	blake3:UlnTYs6C9_nUjg40WXmTPL5SOPv7W8K5PYNHNd1Q2QQ
1772858782823243	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEypgE		item.create	bn-2w1m	{"description":"Codify the field-eval scenarios as deterministic tests: (1) merge into change does not corrupt epoch/main contract, (2) status/check/sync consistency for change workspaces, (3) push/advance safety behavior, (4) PREPARE snapshot with directory entries, and (5) remote-backed create-from-origin smoke flow. Prefer integration tests in maw-cli and maw-workspaces where behavior spans command surfaces. Acceptance: tests fail on current regressions and pass with fixes; CI coverage prevents recurrence.","kind":"task","labels":["testing","changes-model"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"l","title":"Add /tmp-style regression suite for explicit changes lifecycle"}	blake3:nam7V_2x4j1k0bJ8lMi-RmCS8Z9cybRiozNQddyVBGk
