1772901414983508	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEytAE		item.comment	bn-beu5	{"body":"Closed bn-hhc4 after fixing remaining nested-git destroy-capture failure and validating via cargo test -p maw-cli, cargo test -p maw-workspaces --test destroy_gate, and manual /tmp repro with rebuilt maw binary."}	blake3:HEv_GjXrS1Cw7ezlKEwA1EEM1rHHk4VQdpS2hphMDe8
1772916489082594	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEytQE		item.create	bn-4bpk	{"description":"Repro: in a workspace, create nested embedded repo path (e.g. .tmp/sub/.git with no checked-out commit), then run maw ws destroy <ws> --force. Current destroy preflight fails while computing touched patchset with git hash-object on directory entries, aborting before capture and leaving workspace undeleted. Expected: destroy should proceed safely (or refuse with clear actionable reason), never crash on directory-like status entries, and preserve no-data-loss invariants. Acceptance: maw ws destroy --force succeeds in this scenario; workspace is destroyed; regression test added.","kind":"bug","labels":["destroy","safety","changes-model"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"m","title":"Fix standalone destroy --force failure with embedded git dirs"}	blake3:slwCgX__4uSh_5wEsYDaEHlyMR2EuKDFrX_m9ZmqYn8
1772916497781627	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEytgE		item.create	bn-41c3	{"description":"Repro: (1) create change from main, (2) merge workspace into change target (epoch advances to change commit), (3) merge another workspace into default/main. Current cleanup can replay synthetic deletions into ws/default (e.g., 'D src/a.rs') even though main contains the file, leaving default dirty and inconsistent. Expected: default update should preserve real user edits only and never replay missing files that are artifacts of stale default base. Acceptance: mixed-target sequence leaves ws/default clean with all merged files present; regression test added.","kind":"bug","labels":["merge","working-copy","changes-model"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"l","title":"Prevent default workspace phantom deletions after mixed-target merges"}	blake3:80QTbTzW9ed3Ap_mseuRqk1LSP8a7u2BsMLvlLkP1Ps
1772916510716149	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEytwE		item.create	bn-16ee	{"description":"Add integration + unit regression coverage for: (a) standalone destroy --force with embedded nested git dir entries, and (b) change-target then default-target merge sequence that previously left ws/default with phantom deletions. Tests should fail pre-fix and pass post-fix.","kind":"task","labels":["testing","regressions","changes-model"],"parent":"bn-beu5","size":"m","title":"Expand regressions for embedded dirs and mixed-target replay"}	blake3:sIniNDbkA621VT623AtHeCSSnDIZg9KXzTXAddhVfAI
1772917081504774	1	itc:v3:AWKTMnkmSTJyZnQAAAAAQa2vVqtdbcAAAAEyuAE		item.comment	bn-4bpk	{"body":"Fixed standalone destroy --force crash on embedded git directories by making compute_patchset skip unhashable directory entries and by conservatively counting dirty-status paths in destroy preflight. Added regressions in maw-core diff tests and destroy_gate integration test (standalone_destroy_force_handles_uncapturable_embedded_repo_path). Verified with cargo test -p maw-core, cargo test -p maw-cli, cargo test -p maw-workspaces, plus manual /tmp flow."}	blake3:4gGejjCKJz-VCD4GTXW5Qu1IOOq-A_RzOkRVceesEwQ
